(Corrects spelling of Dallaraâ€™s name in second paragraph.)  Talks between the Greek government
and private creditors on a debt swap are in the final stages, a
Greek Finance Ministry official said.  A meeting in  Athens  today between Greek Prime Minister
 Lucas Papademos , Finance Minister Evangelos Venizelos and
Charles Dallara, the managing director of the Washington-based
Institute of International Finance, was positive and productive
and discussions will continue tomorrow, said the official, who
declined to be identified.  European finance ministry representatives will meet in
Brussels today to discuss the debt swap, the Greek official
